# User Manual Maintenance Rule

Use `doc/user-manual.qmd` as the source of truth for user-facing behavior.

## End-of-step checklist (run before completing any substantial work step)

- Check whether changes affect user-visible UI, workflows, labels, controls, shortcuts, or behavior.
- If yes, update `doc/user-manual.qmd` in the same step:
  - Update "Last updated" date.
  - Update relevant usage instructions and examples.
  - Remove instructions that no longer match current behavior.
- If user flows changed significantly, include a short migration note in the manual.
- If no user-facing impact exists, explicitly confirm no user-manual update is required.

## Documentation discipline

- Write for end users, not implementers.
- Prefer step-by-step instructions and concrete action/result phrasing.
